<title>Testing Approach</title><para>The test suite follows these principles:</para>
<para><orderedlist>
<listitem><para><bold>Bias for Action</bold>: Even though these are documentation files, comprehensive validation tests were created to ensure data integrity and consistency.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><bold>Validation Over Generation</bold>: Tests validate structure and content rather than regenerating files, ensuring documentation maintains quality standards.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><bold>Pattern Matching</bold>: Uses regex patterns to extract and validate structured data (timestamps, file counts, dependencies).</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><bold>Cross-Validation</bold>: Tests ensure consistency between related documentation files.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><bold>Reality Checks</bold>: Validates that documented content matches actual codebase structure.</para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
</sect1>
